<div class="zm-item-answer-detail">
<div class="zm-item-answer-author-info">
<a href="javascript:;" name="collapse" class="collapse meta-item zg-right"><i class="z-icon-fold"></i>收起</a>
<h3 class="zm-item-answer-author-wrap">匿名用户</h3></div>
<div class="zm-item-vote-info " data-votecount="32">

<span class="voters">
<span class="user-block"><a data-tip="p$t$lao-hao-nan" href="http://www.zhihu.com/people/lao-hao-nan" class="zg-link" title="虎毛">虎毛</a>、</span><span class="user-block"><a data-tip="p$t$li-ying-xiao-991" href="http://www.zhihu.com/people/li-ying-xiao-991" class="zg-link" title="衣冠禽兽唐三藏">衣冠禽兽唐三藏</a>、</span><span class="user-block"><a data-tip="p$t$zhang-lu-you-74" href="http://www.zhihu.com/people/zhang-lu-you-74" class="zg-link" title="张路又">张路又</a></span>
</span>


<a href="javascript:;" class="more"> 等人赞同</a>


</div>
<div class="zm-item-rich-text" data-resourceid="3044003" data-action="/answer/content">

<div class="fixed-summary zm-editable-content clearfix">有些人用这些网络用语就是想展示高人一等的优越感：<br>“我也是醉了”——<b>智商上的优越感</b>，潜台词是“你太low b了，我都懒得反驳你。”<br>“你国”，“呵呵”——<b>身份地位上的优越感</b>，居高临下的俯视你，潜台词就是“朕知道了，一边玩去。”<br><br>还有一些人想用这些网络用语体现自己的言语犀利、特立独行，岂不知反而千篇一律、毫无新意，还附带让人觉得说话者面目可憎。
<a href="/question/27152734/answer/37730927" class="toggle-expand">显示全部</a>
<div class="fixed-summary-mask"></div>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
